---
import IntakeLayout from "../../../layouts/IntakeLayout.astro";
---

<IntakeLayout
  title="Editorial standards | The Intake"
  description="How The Intake approaches accuracy, independence, and updates for healthcare practice content."
  showBreadcrumb={false}
>
  <div class="max-w-content mx-auto px-4 py-10 sm:px-6 lg:px-12 lg:py-14">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/theintake" class="font-medium text-tebra-teal-dark hover:underline">The Intake</a>
      <span class="mx-2" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span class="text-gray-700">Editorial standards</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="mt-6 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-tebra-teal-dark sm:text-4xl">
      Editorial standards
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-gray-600">
      The Intake publishes practical guidance for independent practices. These standards describe how we aim to keep
      content useful, transparent, and aligned with Tebra’s mission.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-2xl space-y-8 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Accuracy &amp; clarity</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We strive to explain billing, operations, and technology topics in plain language. Regulatory and payer rules
          change frequently; always confirm details with your counsel, payers, and official sources before making
          decisions.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Independence</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The Intake is an editorial hub powered by Tebra. Product mentions may reference Tebra capabilities where
          relevant; we still aim to lead with education that helps practices regardless of vendor.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Updates</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Articles may be revised when guidance or products evolve. Check publish context and related Tebra product
          pages for the latest capabilities.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions or corrections? Reach the team through
          <a href="/contact" class="mx-1 font-semibold text-tebra-teal-dark hover:underline">Contact</a>
          on the main Tebra site.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</IntakeLayout>
